      },
      "date": "2013-11-07 11:02:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nI reproduced sanity.sh 183 failure with upstream client that uses the same atomic_open code as master. The reason for the failure is when atomic_open passes in hashed negative dentry that is created by other node, we leak the inode and do not instantiate the dentry even if server returns DISP_LOOKUP_POS and DISP_OPEN_OPEN.\n\nsanity.sh 183 fails the same path because occasionally it causes client to create false negative dentry in dcache after doing error sim testing and resetting fail_loc.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
